pageContext.claim: “And the average price of gasoline is $2 and even a little bit below $2 a gallon. Something you have never thought possible. And yet we have a vibrant energy sector, vibrant like you haven't seen.”
pageContext.analysis: The president should check his sourcing. Gasoline prices did drop to around $1.93 in April, but were closer to $2.30 in July, {according to the U.S. Energy Information Association.}
